  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. Substituting <math><mn>9</mn></math> for <math><mi>x</mi></math> and <math><mn>0</mn></math> for <math><mi>y</mi></math> in the first inequality gives <math><mn>0</mn><mo>&#8804;</mo><mn>14</mn></math>, which is true; substituting into the second gives <math><mn>0</mn><mo>&#8805;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>29</mn></math>, which is true. Therefore, (9, 0) is a solution. Choice B fails the first inequality (0 \u2264 -4 is false). Choice C fails the first inequality (9 \u2264 5 is false). Choice D fails the second inequality (-9 \u2265 -2 is false).</p>",
